  "text": "# Kubernetes Informer Cache Event Handler Chain\n\nThe event handler chain in Kubernetes client-go traces the path from API server watch events to informer cache updates through the following components and flow:\n\n## 1. ListWatch (tools/cache/listwatch.go)\nThe `ListWatch` struct implements the `ListerWatcher` interface with two functions:\n- `ListFunc`: Performs initial list of resources from API server\n- `WatchFunc`: Establishes a watch connection to receive subsequent API server events\n\nThese are created via `NewListWatchFromClient()` which wraps REST client calls to the API server.\n\n## 2. Reflector (tools/cache/reflector.go)\nThe `Reflector` struct watches a specified resource via the `ListerWatcher` and reflects all changes into a `Store`. It:\n- Calls `ListWatch.List()` to get initial resource list\n- Calls `ListWatch.Watch()` to establish watch stream from API server\n- Converts API server watch events into store operations (Add, Update, Delete)\n- Feeds events into the `DeltaFIFO` queue\n\n## 3. DeltaFIFO Queue (tools/cache/delta_fifo.go)\nThe `DeltaFIFO` is a queue implementation that accumulates deltas for each object. Key components:\n- `Delta`: Represents a single change with `Type` (Added, Updated, Deleted, Replaced, Sync) and `Object`\n- `Deltas`: A list of Delta objects for a single resource\n- `DeltaFIFO.Pop()`: Returns accumulated Deltas objects for processing\n- Deduplicates and accumulates changes before dispatching\n\n## 4. Controller & ProcessFunc (tools/cache/controller.go)\nThe `Controller` manages the reflector and processes queue items:\n- Creates a `Reflector` to feed watch events into `DeltaFIFO`\n- Repeatedly pops `Deltas` from the queue\n- Calls `ProcessFunc` (configured in Config) with each Deltas object\n- The `processDeltas()` function:\n  - Iterates through each Delta in the Deltas list\n  - Updates the local cache (clientState Store)\n  - Calls `ResourceEventHandler` methods: `OnAdd()`, `OnUpdate()`, `OnDelete()`\n  - Passes the handler to the sharedIndexInformer for notification dispatch\n\n## 5. SharedIndexInformer Handler Dispatch (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)\nThe `sharedIndexInformer` implements `ResourceEventHandler` and acts as a handler in processDeltas():\n- `HandleDeltas()` receives the Deltas from controller\n- `OnAdd()`: Called for added resources, calls `processor.distribute(addNotification{...})`\n- `OnUpdate()`: Called for updated resources, calls `processor.distribute(updateNotification{...})`\n- `OnDelete()`: Called for deleted resources, calls `processor.distribute(deleteNotification{...})`\n- Updates the local indexer/cache\n- Dispatches notifications to all registered event handlers via the sharedProcessor\n\n## 6. Notification Distribution (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)\nThe `sharedProcessor` distributes notifications to all registered listeners:\n- `addListener()`: Registers a new event handler with a `processorListener` wrapper\n- `distribute()`: Sends notification objects (addNotification, updateNotification, deleteNotification) to all listeners\n  - Non-sync notifications go to all listeners\n  - Sync notifications only go to listeners that are currently syncing\n\n## 7. Processor Listener & Handler Invocation (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)\nEach `processorListener` represents a single registered event handler:\n- `add()`: Receives notification from sharedProcessor\n- `pop()`: Runs in a separate goroutine, buffers notifications in a ring buffer (pendingNotifications)\n- Transfers notifications from addCh to nextCh while waiting for the handler to consume them\n- `run()`: Runs in another goroutine, receives notifications from nextCh\n  - For `addNotification`: calls `handler.OnAdd(obj, isInInitialList)`\n  - For `updateNotification`: calls `handler.OnUpdate(oldObj, newObj)`\n  - For `deleteNotification`: calls `handler.OnDelete(obj)`\n\n## 8. Cache Store (tools/cache/store.go)\nThe `Store` interface and `cache` implementation provide thread-safe storage:\n- Maintains key-to-object mapping\n- Supports Add(), Update(), Delete(), Get(), List() operations\n- Used by both the DeltaFIFO (as knownObjects) and sharedIndexInformer (as indexer)\n- Updates happen before handler notifications are dispatched\n\n## Flow Summary\nAPI Server Watch Events → ListWatch.Watch() → Reflector → DeltaFIFO → Controller.Run() → processDeltas() → sharedIndexInformer.OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete() → sharedProcessor.distribute() → processorListener.add() → processorListener.pop() → processorListener.run() → Registered ResourceEventHandler callback"
